text: Always pleasant....we love their pizza. Although I wish we could get regular crust instead of thin on the $5.99 Friday pizza. My husband has been eating PM for years and does not like thin crust. I prefer it so usually get my own pizza. üòÄ Overall we love them.

text: Fresh ingredients, and  fast & friendly service.  We like the Gourmet Veggie & we sub red sauce for the creamy, & plus a few additions & omissions on the standard toppings.  They make our changes flawlessly.

name: Macie Akona
text: Service was fast, and very friendly. The woman that helped me today even offered to carry my order to my car for me because she saw I was carrying my baby‚Äôs car seat. I‚Äôve never had an employee go above and beyond like that. Pizza was delicious too!

text: This team is on it. They make a chain look like a home town family business. They are very personable and always have orders correct!  In short, they are awesome.

text: Great pizzas. Can custom make too. Love pizza!

name: Teri Lindell
text: Good thick dough, perfect crisp on the crust, and the ingredients. ..fresh, meaty, ample, and cozi delicioso! Bit of a wait but worth it. Friendly guys.

name: Kurt
text: Friendly staff. Quality Papa Murphy's Pizza. Highly recommend the Cowboy pizza, especially when it's a special. Phoned in order and ready when arrived, but have also ordered online.

name: Jon Rutlen
text: Employees are not required to wear masks during the covid-19 pandemic

text: Out of all the Papa Murphy's around town, this one is by far superior! The ingredients are always fresh, the pizza is always made the way you want it (no mistakes), and it is always delicious!
